EXTENDED OUTLOOK
MONDAY TO THURSDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND
COASTGUARD AGENCY AT 212300 UTC
LARGE AND DEEP AREAS OF LOW PRESSURE REMAIN DOMINANT
DURING THIS PERIOD. DURING MONDAY EVENING A VERY DEEP
LOW 939 IS EXP TO BE CENTRED OVER THE N OF SEA AREA
ROCKALL. THIS LOW MOVS SLWY NE TO LIE OVER SEA AREA
HEBRIDES 932 BY TUESDAY MORNING AND THEN N TO LIE NEAR
THE FAEROES 939 BY MIDNIGHT ON CHRISTMAS DAY AND THEN FLN
SLWY AS IT MOVS AWAY NWARDS INTO THE NORWEGIAN SEA BY
MIDDAY ON BOXING DAY. BY BOXING DAY EVENING A NEW VERY
DEEP LOW 950 IS EXP TO APPROACH THE WERN BOUNDARY OF SEA
AREA ROCKALL. STRG WINDS OR GALES ARE EXP IN ALL AREAS
FOR MOST OF THE PERIOD WITH SEV GALES OR STORMS LIKELY AT
TIMES FM MONDAY EVENING TO EARLY ON CHRISTMAS DAY. WINDS
MAINLY FM THE S OR SW. WINDS MAY EASE FOR A TIME LATER ON
CHRISTMAS DAY AND EARLY ON BOXING DAY
